Explore RDF data cube vocabulary

This script explores the RDF data cube vocabulary.

library(rrdfancillary)

The following is just a test for Mermaid. Mermaid can also include links - see (http://knsv.github.io/mermaid/#interaction)

mermaid.commands<- '
graph TB
 qb:Attachable("Attachable(abstract)")
 qb:Observation(Observation)
 qb:Attachable-->|text|qb:Observation
'
DiagrammeR( mermaid.commands )

Load the vocabulary

The vocabulary is loaded in to a rrdf store with support for inferencing (ontology=TRUE). Enabeling the inferencing is an advantage when loading an ontology/vocabulary like the RRDF data cube, as the vocabulary may be made expecting inferencing being used.

qb.fn <- file.path(system.file("extdata/cube-vocabulary-rdf", package="rrdfqb"), "cube.ttl" )
empty.rdf <- new.rdf(ontology=TRUE)
cat("Loading from ", normalizePath(qb.fn), "\n" )

Loading from /home/ma/R/x86_64-redhat-linux-gnu-library/3.3/rrdfqb/extdata/cube-vocabulary-rdf/cube.ttl

qb.rdf<- load.rdf(qb.fn,"TURTLE",empty.rdf)
dump.qb.rq<- paste(
  "SELECT  ?s ?p ?o ",
  "WHERE { ?s ?p ?o }", sep="\n", collapse="\n"
)
cat(dump.qb.rq,"\n")

SELECT ?s ?p ?o WHERE { ?s ?p ?o }

cube.triples<- data.frame(sparql.rdf(qb.rdf, dump.qb.rq ), stringsAsFactors=FALSE)
knitr::kable(cube.triples)

Classes

First the data are loaded into a rrdf store. The code below uses ontology=FALSE as only the directly stated triples are of interest for this.

empty.rdf <- new.rdf(ontology=FALSE)
qb.rdf<- load.rdf(qb.fn,"TURTLE",empty.rdf)
qb.prefix<- '
PREFIX rdf:            <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> 
PREFIX rdfs:           <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> 
PREFIX owl:            <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> 
PREFIX xsd:            <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> 
PREFIX skos:           <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> 
PREFIX foaf:           <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/> 
PREFIX scovo:          <http://purl.org/NET/scovo#> 
PREFIX void:           <http://rdfs.org/ns/void#> 
PREFIX qb:             <http://purl.org/linked-data/cube#> 
PREFIX dcterms:        <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> 
'

Getting an overview of the classes is done as shown below, as suggested in “Learning SPARQL”.

dump.classes.all.rq<- '
SELECT * 
WHERE 
{ 
  ?class a rdfs:Class .
  ?class a ?classType
}
'
cat(dump.classes.all.rq,"\n")

SELECT * WHERE { ?class a rdfs:Class . ?class a ?classType }

classes.all.df<- data.frame(sparql.rdf(qb.rdf, paste( qb.prefix, dump.classes.all.rq, sep="\n" )), stringsAsFactors=FALSE)
knitr::kable(classes.all.df)

qb:SliceKey rdfs:Class

For the present purpose only the class names are of interest.

dump.classes.distinct.rq<- '
SELECT DISTINCT ?class ?label
WHERE 
{ 
  ?class a rdfs:Class .
  ?class a ?classType .
  OPTIONAL {?class rdfs:label ?label}
}
'
cat(dump.classes.distinct.rq,"\n")

SELECT DISTINCT ?class ?label WHERE { ?class a rdfs:Class . ?class a ?classType . OPTIONAL {?class rdfs:label ?label} }

classes.distinct.df<- data.frame(sparql.rdf(qb.rdf, paste( qb.prefix, dump.classes.distinct.rq, sep="\n" )), stringsAsFactors=FALSE)
knitr::kable(classes.distinct.df)
class label
qb:Attachable Attachable (abstract)
qb:AttributeProperty Attribute property
qb:Observation Observation
qb:ComponentSpecification Component specification
qb:DimensionProperty Dimension property
qb:MeasureProperty Measure property
qb:DataSet Data set
qb:SliceKey Slice key
qb:DataStructureDefinition Data structure definition

qb:ComponentProperty Component property (abstract)
qb:HierarchicalCodeList Hierarchical Code List
qb:Slice Slice
qb:ObservationGroup Observation Group
qb:ComponentSet Component set

For the present purpose only the class names are of interest.

dump.classes.subClassOf.rq<- '
SELECT DISTINCT ?class ?subClassOf 
WHERE 
{ 
  ?class a rdfs:Class .
  ?class rdfs:subClassOf ?subClassOf .
FILTER ( ?subClassOf != rdf:Property )
}
'
cat(dump.classes.subClassOf.rq,"\n")

SELECT DISTINCT ?class ?subClassOf WHERE { ?class a rdfs:Class . ?class rdfs:subClassOf ?subClassOf . FILTER ( ?subClassOf != rdf:Property ) }

classes.subClassOf.df<- data.frame(sparql.rdf(qb.rdf, paste( qb.prefix, dump.classes.subClassOf.rq, sep="\n" )), stringsAsFactors=FALSE)
knitr::kable(classes.subClassOf.df)
class subClassOf
qb:AttributeProperty qb:ComponentProperty
qb:Observation qb:Attachable
qb:ComponentSpecification qb:ComponentSet
qb:DimensionProperty qb:CodedProperty
qb:DimensionProperty qb:ComponentProperty
qb:MeasureProperty qb:ComponentProperty
qb:DataSet qb:Attachable
qb:SliceKey qb:ComponentSet
qb:DataStructureDefinition qb:ComponentSet
qb:CodedProperty qb:ComponentProperty
qb:Slice qb:Attachable
qb:Slice qb:ObservationGroup

Finally, generate the mermaid commands for showing the class structure.

mermaid.commands<- paste(
           "graph TB", 
           paste( classes.distinct.df$class,'("', classes.distinct.df$label, '")', sep="", collapse=";\n" ),
          paste( classes.subClassOf.df$subClassOf, "-->", classes.subClassOf.df$class, sep="", collapse=";\n" ),
          sep=" \n", collapse="\n")

Domain and range with properties

The query below removes the blank nodes, as it only occurs for the qb:codeList.

dump.drp.rq<- '
SELECT DISTINCT ?domain ?property ?range # ( !isBlank(?range) as ?b)
WHERE 
{ 
  ?property a rdf:Property .
  ?property rdfs:domain ?domain .
  ?property rdfs:range ?range .
FILTER (  !isBlank(?range) )
}
'
cat(dump.drp.rq,"\n")

SELECT DISTINCT ?domain ?property ?range # ( !isBlank(?range) as ?b) WHERE { ?property a rdf:Property . ?property rdfs:domain ?domain . ?property rdfs:range ?range . FILTER ( !isBlank(?range) ) }

drp.df<- data.frame(sparql.rdf(qb.rdf, paste( qb.prefix, dump.drp.rq, sep="\n" )), stringsAsFactors=FALSE)
knitr::kable(drp.df)
domain property range
qb:Slice qb:sliceStructure qb:SliceKey
qb:ComponentSpecification qb:componentAttachment rdfs:Class
qb:DataSet qb:structure qb:DataStructureDefinition
qb:ComponentSpecification qb:order xsd:int
qb:Observation qb:dataSet qb:DataSet
qb:ComponentProperty qb:concept skos:Concept

Finally, generate the mermaid commands for showing the class structure.

mermaid.commands<- paste(
           "graph TB", 
           paste( drp.df$domain,'("', drp.df$domain, '")', sep="", collapse=";\n" ),
           paste( drp.df$range,'("', drp.df$range, '")', sep="", collapse=";\n" ),
          paste( drp.df$domain, "-->", '|"', drp.df$property, '"|', drp.df$range, sep="", collapse=";\n" ),
          sep=" \n", collapse="\n")
